5.  **Newline after Row:** After the inner loop completes (meaning all columns in the current row have been printed), `std::endl` is used to insert a newline character, moving the cursor to the beginning of the next line. This ensures that subsequent rows of the array are printed on new lines, maintaining the two-dimensional structure in the output.

